Reactpagination Notes :
forcePage={currentPage}: Ensures the UI stays in sync with your state.
onPageChange: Updates currentPage when a user clicks.
pageCount: Tells the component how many pages to render.
pageRangeDisplayed & marginPagesDisplayed: Control the number of visible pagination buttons.
breakLabel: Adds a "..." for skipped pages.
previousClassName / nextClassName: Allow disabling navigation arrows when at bounds.